WORK SUMMARY :
The session began with an introduction to REST APIs. We learned that REST (Representational State Transfer) is an architectural style used for building web services that 
communicate over HTTP. The trainer explained how REST APIs allow applications to interact with servers by sending requests and receiving responses, usually in JSON format.
This helped us understand how frontend and backend systems communicate in real-world application followed by API Testing using Postman, as part of the web development
training program.


LEARNING OUTCOMES :
Understood the fundamentals of REST APIs and client-server communication
Learned how to test APIs using Postman
